"Currently, Gekko's 4 Globule variants all limited QoL for where they land after their respective ability ends.

For Wingman and Thrash this is rarely an issue, as both abilities are ground-level for the most part... you kind of have to intentionally go out of your way to land them on an inaccessible high-ground by their very nature.

But for Dizzy, and in particular high flying Mosh Globule...

They can inconsistently get stuck on random geometry or more often just normal high-ground boxes, and become inaccessible to Gekko through normal gameplay.

Unlike other projectile utility agents like Kayo for whom weird clipping is annoying but only ruins one ability cast, Gekko needs to make use of his pickup mechanic to get full value from his kit.

A substantial chunk of his value comes from being able to pick up his abilities and go again. Can't do that if you hit some random geometry outside the play space and that time it sticks instead of bouncing back to playable space as intended.
3 different examples of the QoL problems on live right now.

Very similar utility throws result in very different outcomes. One thrown Dizzy behaves properly and falls back into the play space so Gekko is able to pick it up again. The other instead clips onto inaccessible geometry outside the play space and forms the globule there, even though its not a surface other interactables can land or be placed on [think Killjoy turret, Veto teleport, Chamber teleport, etc].

The spike however correctly checks if the surface is a ""ground level"" surface, and falls back into the playspace. My suggestion is to simply have Gekko's globules run the same logic, such that they are always put back into the play space when hitting inaccessible [or movement ability only, see #3] geometry. Best case scenario it does nothing, and the current tumble mechanics work as intended. Worst case scenario, now at least the globule is within the playspace even if it might not be the closest spot to fall to... after all that is far better than you being completely incapable of doing so due to inconsistent geometry clipping.

2. Currently when picking up Globules, the game keeps checking if you maintain line of sight to the centre of the globule. However Gekko always crouches down when picking up Globules, regardless of what height they are located at. So often with head level boxes you can reach the globule, but when you interact with it, you are forced to crouch, which then breaks line of sight to the center thus interrupting itself. My suggestion is to only check for line of sight to start picking up a globule, to avoid this issue entirely.

3. Like I talked about with the first point, Dizzy and Mosh can often get stuck on ability required high-ground [otherwise inaccessible via normal movement]. In practice this is the same problem, but its also resolved using the existing spike mechanics. If you drop a spike onto somewhere you can't access without using an ability, then it automatically falls back into the play-space. Same mechanic should apply to Globules. No complex changes required.

These two proposed changes will easily and efficiently improve quality of life without changing ability balance, and avoid a common pain point when using Gekko's utility on the fly.",Insight,
