To maximize the visible screen area, many players utilize the maximum Field of View (FOV) and adjust viewmodel offsets to minimize the visual footprint of their own weapon.High refresh rate monitors (240Hz and 360Hz) have become the baseline, with OLED technology gaining ground due to its superior motion clarity and instantaneous response times.

Tactical Adaptation and the 2026 Competitive Ecosystem
The meta-environment of 2026 has been defined by a significant reduction in the impact of utility, shifting the focus back to individual gunfighting prowess.

Utility Nerfs and the ""Gunfight Meta""
Recent balance updates have significantly nerfed sentinel and initiator utility. Vyse and Cypher have seen reductions in their area-denial capabilities, and the overall volume of flashes and stuns has been decreased across the board.This has led to a meta where ""get-out"" duelists like Yoru and Jett are highly valued for their ability to take aggressive duels and escape if they fail to secure the kill.

