Conclusions and Practical Recommendations
The data and professional standards of 2026 indicate that the optimization of aim is an integrated process requiring attention to technical, physical, and tactical details. For players seeking to emulate professional performance, the following recommendations are suggested:

Standardize hardware to minimize input latency, prioritizing 1600 DPI with low in-game sensitivity and ensuring the use of a Raw Input Buffer. Select a mouse grip and ergonomic setup that supports long-term health and kinetic stability, specifically focusing on the claw grip for its versatile performance characteristics.

