"For the evaluation, I took one player of each rank with average stats (around 1.0–1.1 K/D) and their last 10 matches (excluding 5-stacks, games with obvious smurf, and matches with unrated players).

100 matches were fed into an AI, which calculated how an average player of a higher rank performs when placed in a match against a lobby one rank lower.

Improvement is calculated using the geometric mean of K/D, ACS, KAST, and ADR.

Rd → I3: 1.31x / number of such cases: 12
I3 → I2: 1.25x / 33
I2 → I1: 1.13x / 51
I1 → A3: 1.09x / 12
A3 → A2: 1.10x / 19
A2 → A1: 1.26x / 15
A1 → D3: 1.05x / 15
D3 → D2: 1.14x / 12
D2 → D1: 1.09x / 9

The three real walls in high elo are Radiant, Immortal 3, and Ascendant 2.
Ascendant 1 and Diamond 3 are nearly identical in performance.
Most other rank transitions show a steady 9–14% improvement per tier.

The sample is certainly small, but the trend is visible and corresponds to rank distribution.",Insight,
"If you are Iron - Silver, I suggest you listen to this.
1. Stop filling
I promise you that team comp does not matter in this elo at all. There are a lot of low elo players who play a wide variety of agents that they have little knowledge of. Stop doing this. You should ideally main 2 agents maximum that you like and are comfortable with.

2. Stop Playing too little or too many games a day
Many low elo players either play 2 games a day or 10+ games a day. Stop doing this. You ideally want you play 3 games minimum to 6 games maximum a day. Playing way too many games a day with make you susceptible to tilt queuing and you won't rank up significantly if you play too little games a day.

3. Improve your mechanics
I promise you that nothing else matters in low elo besides mechanics. The best way to improve your mechanics is to go in the range and try to hit bots on medium mode while counter strafing or play deathmatch and unbind your crouch button. Also if you are going to play deathmatch, use guns like the sheriff and guardian since they incentivize first shot accuracy and crosshair placement.

4. Have good coms
You don't even have to IGL. Telling your teammates where the enemies are, what utility they used and where, as well as how much damage you dealt to them will win you a lot more rounds than you think.

Anyways, These are the tips that got me out of low elo, if they worked for me they could work for you as well.",Insight,
