"Harbor Ability Changes Ideas (Will these changes help the only 3 Harbor mains in the world find companionship?)
Discussion
Harbor's main issue is his unreliable map control due to the limitations of his smoke and wall. He can only provide a single orb smoke for teammates across the map. Lurking has its drawbacks cus his wall is vital for site execs, yet it has a limited range and gives away his position when deployed. He also has limited playmaking potential that can be done with Storm Surge. So, here are my solutions to fix these issues:

[C] Storm Surge (nearsight): Functions the same, except it no longer produces a sound cue when it hits enemies. The ability now has 2 charges.

[Q] Cove (shield): Functions the same as the pre-rework version. It is a throwable that deploys as a smoke orb, and reactivating the ability adds a shield to it.

[E] High Tide (line wall): Activating lets Harbor enter Astral Form (similar to Astra), allowing him to place the wall anywhere on the map while keeping the ability to control its trajectory. It has a 45s CD.

[X] Reckoning (ult): Functions the same, except its width is increased from 21m to 32m. Additionally, the duration when stopped is increased from 7s to 10s.

My Thinking:
These changes help Harbor break out of being effective only as a secondary controller (random bs concept btw), which IMO, is a poor excuse for bad design (no offense :P). This also solidifies his identity as a line smoker which is plus aura points to his initiator pals.

The High Tide change borrows Astra's deployment mechanic instead of Omen's, allowing Harbor to place the wall anywhere on the map, making it more versatile while keeping its beloved and unique gimmick. I've given Storm Surge 2 charges to improve our friendo's offensive punch and also to compensate the fact I removed its sound cue.

I reverted Cove to its pre-rework version for the sake of simplicity and quickness. Reckoning is actually a good design, but it losses points in the menacing aura department of how an ult should have. With the ult change, players will have the option to effectively slice the site in half.

What do you all think? How would you rework Harbor?",Insight,
